n|Stemmer|Rodeike|Bock|2002|p=80}}\n|-\n| 47\n| 5 November 1940\n| 14:40\n| Spitfire\n| northeast of Portland{{sfn|Prien|Stemmer|Rodeike|Bock|2002|p=80}}\n| style=\"border-left: 3px solid grey;\" | 54\n| 10 November 1940\n| 15:43\n| Spitfire\n| east of Portsmouth{{sfn|Prien|Stemmer|Rodeike|Bock|2002|p=80}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#fbec5d;\" | 48\u2660\n| 6 November 1940\n| 15:35\n| Hurricane\n| Southampton{{sfn|Prien|Stemmer|Rodeike|Bock|2002|p=80}}\n| style=\"border-left: 3px solid grey;\" | 55\n| 28 November 1940\n| 15:10\n| Spitfire\n| northeast of the Isle of Wight{{sfn|Prien|Stemmer|Rodeike|Bock|2002|p=80}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#fbec5d;\" | 49\u2660\n| 6 November 1940\n| 15:37\n| Hurricane\n| Southampton{{sfn|Prien|Stemmer|Rodeike|Bock|2002|p=80}}\n| style=\"border-left: 3px solid grey;\" | 56\n| 28 November 1940\n| 17:13\n| Spitfire\n| Bournemouth{{sfn|Prien|Stemmer|Rodeike|Bock|2002|p=80}}<br />vicinity of the Isle of Wight\n|}\n\n===Awards===\n[[File:Helmut Wick EK I und Eichenlaub Stecknadel.JPG|thumb|right|upright=0.8|Wick's Iron Cross and Oak Leaves pin (family possession)]]\n* [[Iron Cross]] (1939) \n** 2nd Class (21 December 1939){{sfn|Thomas|1998|p=441}}\n** 1st Class (6 June 1940){{sfn|Thomas|1998|p=441}}\n* [[Pilot/Observer Badge]] in Gold with Diamonds\n* [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]]\n** Knight's Cross on 27 August 1940 as ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' and ''[[Staffelkapit\u00e4n]]'' of the 3./''Jagdgeschwader'' 2 \"Richthofen\"{{sfn|Scherzer|2007|p=783}}{{sfn|Fellgiebel|2000|p=445}}\n** 4th Oak Leaves on 6 October 1940 as ''[[Major (Germany)|Major]]'' and ''[[Gruppenkommandeur]]'' of the I./''Jagdgeschwader'' 2 \"Richthofen\"{{sfn|Fellgiebel|2000|p=53}}{{refn|According to Scherzer on 25 October 1940.{{sfn|Scherzer|2007|p=783}}|group=\"Note\"}}\n* Five named references in the ''[[Wehrmachtbericht]]'' (26 August 1940, 6 October 1940, 8 November 1940, 16 November 1940 and 4 December 1940){{sfn|''Die Wehrmachtberichte 1939\u20131945 Band 1''|pp=288, 321, 354, 361, 375}}\n\n===Dates of rank===\n{| style=\"background: transparent;\"\n|-\n| 8 November 1938: || ''[[Leutnant]]'' (Second Lieutenant){{sfn|Stockert|2012|p=37}}\n|-\n| 21 July 1940: || ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' (First Lieutenant){{sfn|Stockert|2012|p=37}}\n|-\n| 4 September 1940: || ''[[Hauptmann]]'' (Captain){{sfn|Stockert|2012|p=37}}\n|-\n| 19 October 1940: || ''[[Major (Germany)|Major]]'' (Major){{sfn|Stockert|2012|p=38}}\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=\"Note\"}}\n\n==References==\n===Citations===\n{{Reflist|25em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{Refbegin|30em}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Bergstr\u00f6m\n  |first=Christer\n  |year=2015\n  |title=The Battle of Britain: An Epic Conflict Revisited\n  |location=Oxford, UK\n  |publisher=Casemate\n  |isbn=978-1612-00347-4\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Collier\n  |first=Richard\n  |year=1980\n  |title=Eagle Day: The Story of the Battle of Britain\n  |location=Oxford, UK\n  |publisher=Horizon\n  |isbn=978-0525096504\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Fellgiebel\n  |first=Walther-Peer\n  |authorlink=Walther-Peer Fellgiebel\n  |year=2000\n  |origyear=1986\n  |title=Die Tr\u00e4ger des Ritterkreuzes des Eisernen Kreuzes 1939\u20131945 \u2014 Die Inhaber der h\u00f6chsten Auszeichnung des Zweiten Weltkrieges aller Wehrmachtteile\n  |trans-title=The Bearers of the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross 1939\u20131945 \u2014 The Owners of the Highest Award of the Second World War of all Wehrmacht Branches\n  |language=German\n  |location=Friedberg, Germany\n  |publisher=Podzun-Pallas\n  |isbn=978-3-7909-0284-6\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Foreman\n  |first=John\n  |year=1988\n  |title=Battle of Britain: The Forgotten Months, November And December 1940\n  |location=London, UK\n  |publisher=Air Research Publications\n  |isbn=978-1-871187-02-1\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Franks\n  |first=Norman\n  |year=1997\n  |title=Royal Air Force Fighter Command Losses of the Second Worl