ith Diamonds\n* [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves]]\n** Knight's Cross on 27 August 1940 as ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' and ''[[Staffelkapit\u00e4n]]'' of the 3./''Jagdgeschwader'' 2 \"Richthofen\"{{sfn|Scherzer|2007|p=783}}{{sfn|Fellgiebel|2000|p=445}}\n** 4th Oak Leaves on 6 October 1940 as ''[[Major (Germany)|Major]]'' and ''[[Gruppenkommandeur]]'' of the I./''Jagdgeschwader'' 2 \"Richthofen\"{{sfn|Fellgiebel|2000|p=53}}{{refn|According to Scherzer on 25 October 1940.{{sfn|Scherzer|2007|p=783}}|group=\"Note\"}}\n* Five named references in the ''[[Wehrmachtbericht]]'' (26 August 1940, 6 October 1940, 8 November 1940, 16 November 1940 and 4 December 1940){{sfn|''Die Wehrmachtberichte 1939\u20131945 Band 1''|pp=288, 321, 354, 361, 375}}\n\n===Dates of rank===\n{| style=\"background: transparent;\"\n|-\n| 8 November 1938: || ''[[Leutnant]]'' (Second Lieutenant){{sfn|Stockert|2012|p=37}}\n|-\n| 21 July 1940: || ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' (First Lieutenant){{sfn|Stockert|2012|p=37}}\n|-\n| 4 September 1940: || ''[[Hauptmann]]'' (Captain){{sfn|Stockert|2012|p=37}}\n|-\n| 19 October 1940: || ''[[Major (Germany)|Major]]'' (Major){{sfn|Stockert|2012|p=38}}\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=\"Note\"}}\n\n==References==\n===Citations===\n{{Reflist|25em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{Refbegin|30em}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Bergstr\u00f6m\n  |first=Christer\n  |year=2015\n  |title=The Battle of Britain: An Epic Conflict Revisited\n  |location=Oxford, UK\n  |publisher=Casemate\n  |isbn=978-1612-00347-4\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Collier\n  |first=Richard\n  |year=1980\n  |title=Eagle Day: The Story of the Battle of Britain\n  |location=Oxford, UK\n  |publisher=Horizon\n  |isbn=978-0525096504\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Fellgiebel\n  |first=Walther-Peer\n  |authorlink=Walther-Peer Fellgiebel\n  |year=2000\n  |origyear=1986\n  |title=Die Tr\u00e4ger des Ritterkreuzes des Eisernen Kreuzes 1939\u20131945 \u2014 Die Inhaber der h\u00f6chsten Auszeichnung d